# Implementation Plan - Blog Detail Pages and 4-Blog Content Setup

This plan details the steps to create **Blog Detail Pages** (with a clean, editorial layout matching the style of Image #67) for a total of **4 blog posts**, integrating them into the existing state-based hash router.

## Context
The user requested adding blog detail pages (similar in styling to the project detail pages) and expanding the thoughts/blog section to support a total of 4 blog posts.

## Recommended Approach

### 1. Define 4 Blog Posts Data
We will create a comprehensive data structure for 4 distinct blog posts:
1. `building-trust` (Building Trust Through Clear Design)
2. `art-direction` (The Role of Art Direction in Branding)
3. `scaling-startups` (Scaling Start-ups for Rapid Growth)
4. `intentional-ux` (Intentional UX: The Art of Restraint)

Each post will have:
- Title, date, slug, and category metadata.
- A high-quality placeholder image.
- Rich editorial copy (3-4 paragraphs split into readable columns).

### 2. Extend Hash-Based Router (`src/App.tsx`)
- Update the router in `App.tsx`:
  - If the hash starts with `#/blog/`, parse the `blogId` (slug) and render the new `<BlogDetail blogId={blogId} />` component.
  - Keep Navbar and Footer visible on the blog detail page.

### 3. Connect Thoughts Grid (`src/sections/Thoughts.tsx`)
- In `Thoughts.tsx`:
  - Update the two blog post card containers to be `motion.a` components linking to their respective hash paths (`href={`#/blog/${post.slug}`}`).
  - Map the third card (Dark CTA Card)'s button `"Read Blog"` to point to the first blog post (`#/blog/building-trust`) or the blog route, allowing navigation.

### 4. Create Blog Detail Component (`src/sections/BlogDetail.tsx`)
- Create a new component `src/sections/BlogDetail.tsx` that:
  - Displays the active blog post using a clean, editorial layout.
  - Renders a large header image.
  - Renders the post content across 2 columns (using Archivo 400).
  - Displays a "More Articles" section at the bottom, listing cards for the other 3 blog posts so the user can easily browse all 4 blogs.
  - Automatically scrolls to the top of the window on mount.

## Critical Files to Create/Modify
- `src/sections/BlogDetail.tsx` (New file)
- `src/sections/Thoughts.tsx` (Update to use `motion.a` links and slug data)
- `src/App.tsx` (Update routing logic to handle `#/blog/`)

## Verification Plan
1. **Compilation Check**: Run `npm run build` to verify the code compiles without warnings.
2. **Local Preview**: Run `npm run dev`, verify that clicking any blog card on the landing page opens the correct blog detail page, and all 4 blogs are accessible via the "More Articles" section at the bottom.
